Last month, Environment Minister Mark H Durkan gave his approval to the Belfast Metropolitan Area Plan (BMAP), without the agreement of all other ministers.

"The council welcomes the implementation of the plan to bring to light the issue of air pollutants on residential properties," said Durkan. "The BMRAP will promote air quality control among tenants in the area where it is required and has been implemented. For some buildings, such as an in-store eatery, there is a ban on the consumption of air pollution. BMP will be implementing the policy to prevent air pollution from reaching properties in the area."

